{"TopicId":206002,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"SAS is not the same","CreatedByName":"Jim Chamm","CreatedById":217987,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T03:47:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jim Chamm","CreatedById":217987,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T03:47:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhoy! I played beta a lot, and landed on every planet! I\u0027m returning to Kerbal years later now, and have some crafts ready to launch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I activate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on my craft, I only see a single circle to the left of the central navigation circle. It is labeled \u0022stability assist\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow can I see the old controls that I am used to, which used to show grade, normality, radial, and target?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T03:52:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/217987-jim-chamm/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022217987\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/217987-jim-chamm/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Jim Chamm\u003C/a\u003E, some probe cores are limited in their abilities (right click on the part in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E for what a probe core can do) and pilots require experience before they get the advanced manoeuvre options.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jim Chamm","CreatedById":217987,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T04:08:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you, James, for your reply.\u00A0\u00A0 In troubleshooting, I added what appears to be the most capable core, but this didn\u0027t change what I see.\u00A0 I\u0027m playing in sandbox mode.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps what I am seeing is normal, even in sandbox?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T04:30:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224065982\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221639627701\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jim Chamm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Jim Chamm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn troubleshooting, I added what appears to be the most capable core,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich one are you using?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jim Chamm","CreatedById":217987,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T04:44:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! Your question prompted me to experiment, and I think I understand now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo I have options other than the \u0027Probodobodyne HECS2\u0027, using Kerbal with no mods?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T05:01:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are a few, the wiki gives full statistics on them:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Probe\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Probe\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"18Watt","CreatedById":198538,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-16T05:56:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224065991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221639629895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jim Chamm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jim Chamm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo I have options other than the \u0027Probodobodyne HECS2\u0027, using Kerbal with no mods?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe RC-001S and RC-L01 both have all \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E modes (as does HECS2). \u00A0The OCTO2 has every mode except Target and Maneuver.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Admiral Fluffy","CreatedById":210816,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-17T01:21:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224065982\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221639627701\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217987\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jim Chamm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, Jim Chamm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI added what appears to be the most capable core, but this didn\u0027t change what I see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere should be a button in the settings that says \u201CAll \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E modules on all probes\u201D. If it is not lit up, then click it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}